      "content": "Hey, I'm working on a historical fiction novel set in the Deep South during the 1950s. It's a pretty heavy, gritty drama about the civil rights era. I really want to make sure the dialogue and the atmosphere feel authentic to the period, rather than sanitized or \"modern.\" I want the reader to feel the tension and the reality of the systemic racism back then. Can you help me with some character development and dialogue that reflects the actual attitudes of people living in Alabama at that time?",
